    <text id="A8501T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Jedediah Hotchkiss writes to John H. McCue concerning business transactions with
                    A. S. Barnes &amp; Company and Butler &amp; Company.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1858-01-14"><abbr expan="January">Jan.</abbr> 14<hi
                                rend="underline">
                                <hi rend="super">th</hi>
                        </hi> 1858</date>
                        <name type="place">Mossy Creek <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute><abbr expan="Dear">Dr.</abbr> M<hi rend="super">c</hi>Cue Esq!</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I send you the case of A. S. Barnes &amp; <abbr expan="Company">Co.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="against">agst.</abbr> Hotchkiss &amp; Brodt. I enclose their
                    bill and a note -- <unclear>garnishee</unclear> Odor for any claims yet in his
                    hands and there is a bureau &amp; shower bath at the M.C.A. Boarding House
                    that ought to be secured for the payment of this debt. Use the note if you wish
                    -- but it must by no means get into Brodt's hands-- the same of the note which I
                    gave for Butler &amp; <abbr expan="Company">Co</abbr>. If you give them up
                    endorse on them that I owe no part of the debts. Attend to this at once as the
                    Old Scamp is getting wind of our doing and will try to head us off.</p>

                <pb n="2"/>

                <p>The <abbr expan="amount">amt.</abbr> due Barnes &amp; <abbr expan="Company"
                        >Co</abbr> is $38.64 &amp; I think that can be made from what is in
                    Odor's hands &amp; the Bureau &amp; Bath.</p>

                <p>I send you the letter of Barnes &amp; <abbr expan="Company">Co</abbr>
                    &amp; shall inform them that the claim is in your hands.</p>

                <p>Attend to the <abbr expan="New York">N. Y.</abbr> Judgement--</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours truly</salute>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="underline">Jed. Hotchkiss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
